defaultWritten evidence submitted by defaultSTOPAIDS defaultIntroduction
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSTOPAIDS is the network of 80 UK agencies working since 1986 to secure an effective global response to HIV and AIDS.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe endorse the submission from the Bond Disability
default and Development Working Group and make a few simple points bringing the perspective of a network focused on HIV and AIDS.
default&#xa0;
defaultContext
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDisabled people’s access to information and programmes addressing HIV and AIDS is often inadequate. This flows from a numbe
defaultr of barriers and including: 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultprevailing cultural norms which assume that disabled people do not have sexual identities and/or are not vulnerable to sexual violence which puts them at risk of HIV infection;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultthe inability of mainstream development agencies
default to reach out to and communicate effectively with disabled people;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultthe reluctance of influential agencies such as DFID to fully prioritise the rights of disabled people.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAdditionally, and for the first time since the start of the HIV epidemic 32 years ago, 
default10% of the adult population living with HIV in low- and middle-income countries is aged 50 or older
default. This brings a
defaultn increased need to ensure equitable and sustainable a
defaultccess to affordable, innovative medicines in order to off-set the increased risks of 
defaultmore chronic illnesses and disability
default.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultRecommendations
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn its recent publication, 
defaultTowards Zero Infections – Two Years On
default, 
defaultDFID identifies disabled people as being 
defaulta
default 
default’hard to reach’ group. We therefore 
defaultrecommend that DFID articulate clear goals for how it will use its financial and political influence to advance the position of disabled people in the context of the HIV epidemic in order to (a) increase disabled peopl
defaulte’s access to prevention, treatment, care and support and (b) reduce people’s vulnerability to disability resulting from a lack of e
defaultquitable and sustainable access to affordable, innovative medicines
default.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDrawing on the programmatic experience of our members 
defaultwe specifically recommend:
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultbuilding the capacity of disabled people’s organisations to provide information on HIV/AIDS;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultencouraging the disaggregation of data in all reporting on prevention, treatment and care and support programmes;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultrecognising
default the vulnerability of disabled people, and disabled women and girls in particular, to sexual violence which increases their vulnerability to HIV and AIDS;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultensur
defaulting
default that health facilities are physically and linguistically accessible for disabled people, extending Lynne Featherstone
default’
defaults recent commitment that all new school funded by DFID would be accessible to CWD and extending this to health centres;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultrecognis
defaulting the a
defaultdditional stigma and poverty facing disabled people who are also HIV positive.
